{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Sponsored workers to work for 24hrs per week in a second job ",
        "additional_details": "Advocates for amending current regulations to allow sponsored workers in the UK to work 24 hours per week instead of the current limit of 20 hours, in a second job, think that this would create a win-win scenario for both the workers and the UK economy. We think this could enhance the employment landscape and help foster positive community contributions.\r\n\r\n**Key Reasons That We Think Increasing Work Hours Could Help**\r\n \r\n**Improved Economic Contribution**:\r\n \r\n**Enhanced Integration into the Workforce**:\r\n \r\n**Addressing Labour Shortages**:\r\n \r\n**Support for Flexibility and Well-being**:\r\n \r\n**Increased Tax Revenue**\r\n \r\n**Increased Productivity**\r\n \r\n**Higher Earnings for Workers**\r\n \r\n**Enhanced Business Revenues**\r\n \r\n**Contribution to Tax Revenue**\r\n \r\n**Economic Multiplier effect**",
        "background": "We want the Government to increase the permitted work hours of Sponsored workers from 20hrs to 24hrs per week, in a second job.\r\n",
